CSS Styling Guide Introduction Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML. CSS is designed to enable the separation of presentation and content.
Selectors CSS selectors define which elements to style:
/* Element selector */ p { color: blue; } /* Class selector */ .highlight { background-color: yellow; } /* ID selector */ #header { font-size: 24px; } /* Attribute selector */ input[type=&#34;text&#34;] { border: 1px solid gray; } Box Model The CSS box model describes the rectangular boxes generated for elements:

JavaScript Basics Introduction JavaScript is a programming language that enables interactive web pages. It is an essential part of web applications, and nearly all modern websites use it.
Variables In JavaScript, you can declare variables using var, let, or const:
// Using var (older way) var name = &#34;John&#34;; // Using let (modern way, block-scoped) let age = 30; // Using const (for values that won&#39;t change) const PI = 3.
